able, high-throughput event streaming. Picking the wrong one is a common architectural mistake.', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Kafka vs Redis | Contabo Blog', 'url': 'https://contabo.com/blog/kafka-vs-redis/', 'snippet': 'Pub/Sub Applications: <strong>Redis uses its Pub/Sub capabilities in chat applications, real-time notifications, and queueing systems</strong>. Apache Kafka and Redis both enhance their utility in diverse environments with their design focused on high compatibility ...', 'source': 'brave'}, {'title': 'Redis Streams vs Kafka: A Detailed Comparison', 'url': 'https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-03-31-redis-streams-vs-kafka-detailed-comparison/view', 'snippet': 'A detailed comparison of Redis Streams and Apache Kafka covering consumer groups, ordering, retention, throughput, and when to choose each for event streaming.', 'source': 'brave'}], 'total': 10, 'page': 1, 'error': None}
